    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Extinct group that resembled amphibians but are often not included within the Amphibia class in the most recent classifications. This group contained a great variety of semiaquatic forms such as the snakelike Ophiderpeton, the "horned" Keraterpeton, and the microsaurs, such as Asaphestera. The lepospondylians became extinct during the Pennsylvanian subperiod.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
